main event: An observer reported sighting a glowing red funnel-shaped object traveling across the sky on September 3, 1967.
interesting points: The object was observed traveling at a fast speed with an estimated speed of 800 miles per hour,The observer noted that it moved in a northwesterly direction,Analysis of the photograph indicated it had a blinking or pulsating motion attributed to camera movement,Despite initial observations matching a photograph, it was later determined to be a probable processing blemish,The witness has a background as a professional electronic engineer with relevant training.
witness description: The witness is a 30-year-old male, professional electronic engineer.
